    %% ============================================================================
    %% NOTES
    %% ============================================================================
    %%
    %% TECHNICAL DETAILS:
    %%
    %% 1. Micro-partition Immutability:
    %%    - Snowflake micro-partitions are IMMUTABLE (never modified in place)
    %%    - Any UPDATE/DELETE creates a NEW micro-partition
    %%    - Old partition marked for deletion (removed after Time Travel window)
    %%    - This immutability enables instant cloning
    %%
    %% 2. Metadata-Only Cloning:
    %%    - Clone operation copies ONLY metadata (table definition, pointers)
    %%    - Metadata size: ~1 KB per table (negligible)
    %%    - No data movement across network or storage
    %%    - Cloning 1 GB table takes same time as 1 PB table
    %%
    %% 3. Copy-on-Write Semantics:
    %%    - When clone is modified, affected partitions are copied
    %%    - Only changed partitions cost additional storage
    %%    - Original and clone share unchanged partitions
    %%    - Example: Update 1 row → ~100 MB new partition created
    %%
    %% 4. Storage Cost Attribution:
    %%    - Original table always charged for its data
    %%    - Clone charged only for NEW partitions (diverged data)
    %%    - Shared partitions charged to original (not double-billed)
    %%    - Drop original → clone inherits full storage cost
    %%
    %% 5. Time Travel Interaction:
    %%    - Cloning doesn't reset Time Travel window
    %%    - Clone inherits Time Travel retention setting
    %%    - Can clone FROM a historical point (AT/BEFORE)
    %%    - Both original and clone have independent Time Travel
    %%
    %% LIMITATIONS:
    %% - Can't clone external tables (no Snowflake-managed storage)
    %% - Can't clone temporary tables (session-scoped)
    %% - Can't clone tables with active streams (must drop/recreate)
    %% - Can't clone across regions/accounts (use replication)
    %%
    %% ============================================================================
